BSkyB Directors to Discuss Murdoch’s Future, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   C h r i s   S p i l l a n e
-- 
2011-07-17T05:36:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/bskyb-directors-to-discuss-murdoch-s-future-sunday-times-says.html
British Sky Broadcasting Group Plc (BSY) ,
the U.K.’s largest pay-TV provider, will discuss the future of
its Chairman  James Murdoch  with investors, the Sunday Times
reported, without saying where it got the information.  The company’s independent directors will consult with
shareholders over the next ten days about whether Murdoch should
continue as chairman, the newspaper said. Discussions will be
led by Nick Ferguson, chairman of SVG Capital, according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Spillane in London at 
 cspillane3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at 
 ablackman@bloomberg.net . 